aVSo you won't tell them\u000aat the hotel that the Quaker gentleman is only a tramp after all."
p3104
aV"No, I will say nothing about you."
p3105
aV"I don't think you are to be trusted, boy."
p3106
aV"Did you ever know me to tell a lie, Rudolph?"
p3107
aVasked Tony, proudly.
p3108
aV"I\u000adon't pretend to be a model boy, but there's one thing I won't do, and\u000athat is lie."
p3109
aV"I think I had better make sure that you don't say anything about me,"\u000asaid the tramp, significantly.
p3110
aV"How?"
p3111
aVasked Tony.
p3112
aV"I don't mean to let you go back to the hotel at all."
p3113
aV"But I must go back.
p3114
aVI must drive the horse back."
p3115
aV"That's of no importance."
p3116
aV"Yes, it is," persisted Tony, anxiously.
p3117
aV"They will think I have stolen\u000ait."
p3118
aV"Let them think so."
p3119
aV"But I don't want them to think me a thief."
p3120
aV"I can't help it."
p3121
aV"What are you going to do with me?
p3122
aVWhere are we going?"
p3123
aV"Before I tell you that I will tell you something more.
