aVA handsome and pleasant book."
p6125
aV--_Literary World._\u000a\u000a\u000a     +Search for the Silver City+: A Tale of Adventure in Yucatan.
p6126
aVBy\u000a     JAMES OTIS.
p6127
aV12mo, cloth, price $1.00.
p6128
aVTwo American lads, Teddy Wright and Neal Emery, embark on the steam\u000ayacht Day Dream for a short summer cruise to the tropics.
p6129
aVHomeward\u000abound the yacht is destroyed by fire.
p6130
aVAll hands take to the boats, but\u000aduring the night the boat is cast upon the coast of Yucatan.
p6131
aVThey come\u000aacross a young American named Cummings, who entertains them with the\u000astory of the wonderful Silver City, of the Chan Santa Cruz Indians.
p6132
aVCummings proposes with the aid of a faithful Indian ally to brave the\u000aperils of the swamp and carry off a number of the golden images from\u000athe temples.
p6133
aVPursued with relentless vigor for days their situation is\u000adesperate.
p6134
aVAt last their escape is effected in an astonishing manner.
p6135
