aV"How'd you clean up over here this time, Billy?"
p10338
aVasked the boy in a\u000adry, professional tone.
p10339
aV"Well enough," Mr. Richard Roe answered.
p10340
aV"Went on my uppers once,\u000adown in Mindoro."
p10341
aV"I travel on 'em all the time," said the wan youth.
p10342
aV"Never saw such\u000aluck as I have."
p10343
aV"Get a mascot, Mike," Mr. Richard Roe advised mockingly.
p10344
aV"That's\u000awhat I did.
p10345
aVFinest little mannikin of a mascot the Luck Machine ever\u000aground out.
p10346
