p10354
aVThat's all."
p10355
aVThe aged young man stared at Mr. Richard Roe with dropped jaw.
p10356
aV"Good\u000aLord!"
p10357
aV--his voice was an awe-struck whisper--"that's over a million!"
p10358
aV"Considerably over, theoretically," Mr. Richard Roe agreed, smiling\u000acoolly at the disconcerted young man.
p10359
aV"Unfortunately, Mr. Haines\u000acouldn't cash it all, so I took his notes for everything but a goodly\u000anumber of thou's.
p10360
aVYou may have the notes if you'd like 'em, Mike.
p10361
aVI've got all I want.
p10362
aVAnd get a mascot."
p10363
aVThe aged young man went off into a stream of oaths.
p10364
aV"Where are you\u000agoin' now, Billy?"
p10365
aVhe asked at last.
p10366
aV"Goin'--home?"
p10367
aVHis voice\u000adropped as he spoke the tabooed word, and for a moment, through the\u000alines with which greed and cunning and indulgence had marked him, the\u000aface of a wistful, heart-sick youngster came out dimly.
p10368
aV"_And_ a wife, _and_ a baby?"
p10369
aVsaid Mr. Roe, smiling whimsically.
p10370
aV"No, thank you, Mike.
p10371
aVI'm going over to Siam and buy a small\u000atin-mine.
p10372
aVIt's a thing I've always wanted.
p10373
aVI may breed a line of\u000awhite elephants on the side."
