p11663
aVNever were people so kind; they\u000acared for her comfort as if she had been a favored visitor; they never\u000aallowed her to feel herself _de trop_.
p11664
aVThey accepted her into the bosom\u000aof the family with the most open as well as the most considerate\u000akindness.
p11665
aVNevertheless, it was not very long before Janet began to feel\u000athe creeping in of something not strong enough to be called miasma, a\u000asort of closeness in the air.
p11666
